# Agent tooling — Alfred stack

Provisioned by Alfred. One primary path per task. No ping-pong between similar tools.

## Layer 1 — Native Cursor tools (default)
Use **Read, Grep, Glob, Shell, Edit, Write** for repo work unless a row below names a better primary tool.
If any MCP call errors or takes more than ~5 seconds, **stop using that MCP for the rest of the turn** and fall back to native tools.

## Layer 2 — Domain MCPs (task-specific, not interchangeable)
| Task | Use | Never substitute |
|------|-----|------------------|
| Excel workbook **open** | `excel` (excellm) | excel-mcp |
| Excel **closed** / Power Query / COM | excel-mcp | excel (excellm) |
| Power BI semantic model | powerbi-modeling-mcp | pbi-cli |
| Power BI report / visuals | pbi-cli | powerbi-modeling-mcp |
| GitHub PRs / issues / API | github | filesystem |
| Finance OneDrive (outside repo) | filesystem | native Read/Grep for repo code |
| Library / SDK docs | context7 | fetch, web search |
| Single known URL | fetch | playwright |
| Browser / login / JS UI | playwright | fetch |
| Local PDF / Office → markdown | markitdown | fetch |
| Ad-hoc SQL on CSV/Parquet | duckdb | Excel MCPs |
| Live web search (when `web` bucket installed) | parallel-search | fetch for search |
| **GitHub repo URL to evaluate** | Skill `repo-scout` / `alfred-repo-scout` in current agent (`repo-scout-routing` rule) | casual README skim only; no `repo-*` Task fan-out |
| Supabase / Vercel deploy | supabase / vercel MCP | filesystem |

## Layer 3 — Skills
- **Alfred + third-party skills** live in `~/.agents/skills` (cross-tool standard for Cursor, Claude Code, Codex).
- **Project skills** (`.cursor/skills/` or `.agents/skills/` in repo) — repo-specific only.
Prefer the `~/.agents/skills` copy when both exist.

## Anti-patterns (cause roadblocks)
- Switching excel ↔ excel-mcp mid-task without user action
- Duplicate MCP registration at user + workspace scope (keep user `~/.cursor/mcp.json` only)
